    {
      "id": "8a307e22_ac80878f",
      "file_path": "plugins/plugins-context/plugins-context-schema/plugins-context-schema-avro/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/apex/plugins/context/schema/avro/AvroSchemaMapTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 119,
      "message": "Could probably have been a bit more elegant here ... \nOne main point to note is that the actual parsing error is in the \"Cause\" exception, not in the ContextRuntimeException itself - so not as easy to extract out the message without risking a NullPointerException. \nI think whats there is OK.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5519,
        "name": "John Keeney",
        "display_name": "John Keeney",
        "email": "john.keeney@est.tech",
        "username": "JohnKeeney"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-11 12:37:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "a5a83853_a0fb3d28",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5b8fc0ef_bbd96eea",
      "file_path": "plugins/plugins-context/plugins-context-schema/plugins-context-schema-avro/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/apex/plugins/context/schema/avro/AvroSchemaMapTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 119,
      "message": "I'd switch it to assertThatThrownBy().  Once you've done that, you have a couple of options:\n1) can use isCauseInstanceOf() and hasCauseMessage() (can't remember the exact names)\n2) invoke getCause() which gives back an assertion wrapper on which you can then invoke isInstanceOf() and hasMessage():\n\n  assertThatThrownBy(xxx).getCause().isInstanceOf(yyy).hasMessage(zzz)\n\ndon't have to worry if the cause is null as the wrapper will handle that aspect for you",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
